New Records: Harry Kane became the 10th man to make 100 senior appearances for England and the third to mark the occasion with a goal, after Bobby Charlton and Wayne Rooney. He also extended his lead as England's leading goalscorer at Wembley with his 26th and 27th goals at the stadium.
Key Match Events: Harry Kane scored two goals to secure a 2-0 victory for England against Finland.
Trent Alexander-Arnold created five chances, one of which was scored by Kane.
Ezri Konsa was injured during the match.
Noni Madueke went close to scoring on his England debut.
Post-Match Reflections: Lee Carsley expressed his happiness for Harry Kane, noting his motivation and conduct during the week.
Harry Kane reflected on the significance of his 100th cap and his determination to prove doubters wrong.
Lee Carsley acknowledged being out of his comfort zone during the international break but emphasized the high standards maintained by the team.
Harry Kane praised Lee Carsley's energy and approach, highlighting the freedom and attacking mindset instilled in the team.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Finland fans were vibrant and supportive throughout the match.
England's next matches in the Nations League include fixtures against Greece and the Republic of Ireland.
